\doTocEntry\toclof{}{\csname a:TocLink\endcsname{1}{x1-60002}{}{\numberline {11.13}{\ignorespaces A 1\textsuperscript {st} order Koch curve is constructed by (1) dividing a straight line segment into three segments of equal length; (2) drawing an equilateral triangle that has the middle segment from step 1 as its base and points outward; and (3) removing the line segment that is the base of the triangle from step 2. \relax }}}{168}\relax 
