\doTocEntry\toclof{}{\csname a:TocLink\endcsname{1}{x1-60014}{}{\numberline {11.19}{\ignorespaces The \textbf {Sierpinski carpet} is generated using a recursive algorithm that is built on a grid of eight black squares surrounding a white square. Each level of recursion replaces each black square with the same pattern. From left to right, this figure shows the first four levels of recursion for this algorithm. The end result is an arrangement of small and large holes that shares many characteristics with the size distribution of Finnish lakes shown in Figure~\ref {fig:Finland}.\medskip \relax }}}{169}\relax 
